title: DFM falls on final session of the week
description:
(5 Oct 2017) LEADIN:
The Dubai Financial Market General Index fell by 0.21 percent, closing at 3,591.10 the final session of the week

STORYLINE:
Stocks in the UAE ended the week in the red. 
The Dubai Financial Market General Index fell by 0.21 percent, closing at 3,591.10 points.
Emaar stock fell 0.69 percent 
Brent Crude Oil was selling at 56.42 US dollars a barrel by the end of trade Thursday.
